The two top officials of theChicago Board of Trade, CBT, are planning to visit threecountries in the Far East next month to drum up support for theexchange's proposed night trading session, CBT President ThomasDonovan told Reuters.    Donovan said he and CBT Chairman Karsten Mahlmann willleave April 3 and spend two weeks in Hong Kong, Tokyo andSydney discussing the night trading session with brokeragefirms, regulators and exchanges.    CBT hopes to launch the first U.S. night trading session atthe end of April, offering Treasury-bond and T-note futures andoptions on the two futures contracts between 1700 and 2100 hrscentral U.S. time (2300 to 0300 hrs GMT). Reuter&#3;